{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/59716.To_the_Lighthouse", "title": "To the Lighthouse", "titleComplete": "To the Lighthouse", "description": "The serene and maternal Mrs. Ramsay, the tragic yet absurd Mr. Ramsay, and their children and assorted guests are on holiday on the Isle of Skye. From the seemingly trivial postponement of a visit to a nearby lighthouse, Woolf constructs a remarkable, moving examination of the complex tensions and allegiances of family life and the conflict between men and women.As time winds its way through their lives, the Ramsays face, alone and simultaneously, the greatest of human challenges and its greatest triumph\u2014the human capacity for change.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1639106809i/59716.jpg", "genres": ["School", "Classics", "Feminism", "Modern Classics", "Fiction", "Novels", "Literature", "20th Century", "British Literature", "Literary Fiction"], "asin": "140679239X", "publisher": "Harvest Books", "author": ["Virginia Woolf", "Eudora Welty"], "publishDate": 630748800000, "characters": ["Minta Doyle", "Mrs. Ramsay", "Mrs. McNab", "Rose Ramsay", "Charles Tansley", "James Ramsay", "Jasper Ramsay", "Prue Ramsay", "Cam Ramsay", "William Bankes", "Andrew Ramsay", "Roger Ramsay", "Nancy Ramsay", "Lily Briscoe", "Paul Rayley", "Mr. Ramsay", "Augustus Carmichael"], "places": ["Skye, Inverness-shire, Scotland"], "ratingHistogram": [7017, 15387, 40783, 56818, 57101], "ratingsCount": 177106, "reviewsCount": 12525, "numPages": 209, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Prix Femina - Vie Heureuse", "awardedAt": -1325433600000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/41804.I_Robot", "title": "I, Robot", "titleComplete": "I, Robot (Robot, #0.1)", "description": "Isaac Asimov's I, Robot launches readers on an adventure into a not-so-distant future where man and machine , struggle to redefinelife, love, and consciousness\u2014and where the stakes are nothing less than survival. Filled with unforgettable characters, mind-bending speculation, and nonstop action, I, Robot is a powerful reading experience from one of the master storytellers of our time. I, ROBOT They mustn't harm a human being, they must obey human orders, and they must protect their own existence...but only so long as that doesn't violate rules one and two. With these Three Laws of Robotics, humanity embarked on perhaps its greatest adventure: the invention of the first positronic man. It was a bold new era of evolution that would open up enormous possibilities\u2014and unforeseen risks. For the scientists who invented the earliest robots weren't content that their creations should ' remain programmed helpers, companions, and semisentient worker-machines. And soon the robots themselves; aware of their own intelligence, power, and humanity, aren't either. As humans and robots struggle to survive together\u2014and sometimes against each other\u2014on earth and in space, the future of both hangs in the balance. Human men and women confront robots gone mad, telepathic robots, robot politicians, and vast robotic intelligences that may already secretly control the world. And both are asking the same questions: What is human? And is humanity obsolete? In l, Robot Isaac Asimov changes forever our perception of robots, and human beings and updates the timeless myth of man's dream to play god. with all its rewards\u2014and terrors.--front flap", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1609035271i/41804.jpg", "genres": ["Short Stories", "Classics", "Science Fiction", "Fantasy", "Science Fiction Fantasy", "Audiobook", "Fiction", "Novels", "Robots", "Speculative Fiction"], "asin": "0553803700", "isbn": "0553803700", "isbn13": "9780553803709", "publisher": "Bantam Books", "series": ["Robot, chronological order", "Robot", "Greater Foundation Universe"], "author": ["Isaac Asimov"], "publishDate": 1086073200000, "characters": ["Mike Donovan", "Susan Calvin"], "ratingHistogram": [2078, 8348, 52274, 128986, 147292], "ratingsCount": 338978, "reviewsCount": 9792, "numPages": 224, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/16143347-we-were-liars", "title": "We Were Liars", "titleComplete": "We Were Liars", "description": "A beautiful and distinguished family.A private island.A brilliant, damaged girl; a passionate, political boy.A group of four friends\u2014the Liars\u2014whose friendship turns destructive.A revolution. An accident. A secret.Lies upon lies.True love.The truth. We Were Liars is a modern, sophisticated suspense novel from New York Times bestselling author, National Book Award finalist, and Printz Award honoree E. Lockhart. Read it.And if anyone asks you how it ends, just LIE.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1402749479i/16143347.jpg", "genres": ["Mystery Thriller", "Romance", "Realistic Fiction", "Contemporary", "Mystery", "Audiobook", "Fiction", "Thriller", "Teen", "Young Adult"], "publisher": "Delacorte Press", "series": ["We Were Liars"], "author": ["E. Lockhart"], "publishDate": 1399964400000, "characters": ["Cadence Sinclair"], "places": ["Massachusetts", "Martha's Vineyard, Massachusetts"], "ratingHistogram": [46040, 114688, 285166, 350774, 302531], "ratingsCount": 1099199, "reviewsCount": 106687, "numPages": 242, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Georgia Peach Book Award", "awardedAt": 1420099200000, "category": "", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Pennsylvania Young Readers' Choice Award", "awardedAt": 1451635200000, "category": "Young Adults", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Rhode Island Teen Book Award", "awardedAt": 1451635200000, "category": "", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Milwaukee County Teen Book Award", "awardedAt": 1420099200000, "category": "", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "The Inky Awards", "awardedAt": 1420099200000, "category": "Silver Inky", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Lincoln Award", "awardedAt": 1451635200000, "category": "", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Bookworm Best Award", "awardedAt": 1388563200000, "category": "Best Fiction", "hasWon": nu