{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/14706.Faust_First_Part", "title": "Faust, First Part", "titleComplete": "Faust, First Part", "description": "Goethe\u2019s masterpiece and perhaps the greatest work in German literature, Faust has made the legendary German alchemist one of the central myths of the Western world. Here indeed is a monumental Faust, an audacious man boldly wagering with the devil, Mephistopheles, that no magic, sensuality, experience, or knowledge can lead him to a moment he would wish to last forever. Here, in Faust, Part I, the tremendous versatility of Goethe\u2019s genius creates some of the most beautiful passages in literature. Here too we experience Goethe\u2019s characteristic humor, the excitement and eroticism of the witches\u2019 Walpurgis Night, and the moving emotion of Gretchen\u2019s tragic fate.This authoritative edition, which offers Peter Salm\u2019s wonderfully readable translation as well as the original German on facing pages, brings us Faust in a vital, rhythmic American idiom that carefully preserves the grandeur, integrity, and poetic immediacy of Goethe\u2019s words.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1435405022i/14706.jpg", "genres": ["Poetry", "Classics", "German Literature", "Fantasy", "Fiction", "Philosophy", "Plays", "Literature", "School", "Drama"], "asin": "0553213482", "isbn": "0553213482", "isbn13": "9780553213485", "publisher": "Bantam Classics", "series": ["Goethes Faust"], "author": ["Peter Salm", "Johann Wolfgang von Goethe"], "publishDate": 586422000000, "characters": ["Gretchen", "Faust", "Mephistopheles"], "ratingHistogram": [2130, 5689, 17067, 24948, 24412], "ratingsCount": 74246, "reviewsCount": 1942, "numPages": 327, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Premi de Traducci\u00f3 Vidal Alcover", "awardedAt": 1104566400000, "category": " Jaume Ortol\u00e0 Font", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/285092.High_Fidelity", "title": "High Fidelity", "titleComplete": "High Fidelity", "description": "Do you know your desert-island, all-time, top five most memorable split-ups?Rob does. He keeps a list, in fact. But Laura isn't on it - even though she's just become his latest ex. He's got his life back, you see. He can just do what he wants when he wants: like listen to whatever music he likes, look up the girls that are on his list, and generally behaves as if Laura never mattered. But Rob finds he can't move on. He's stuck in a really deep groove - and it's called Laura. Soon, Rob's asking himself some big questions: about love, about life - and about why we choose to share ours with the people we do.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1327928082i/285092.jpg", "genres": ["Comedy", "Romance", "Humor", "Contemporary", "Adult Fiction", "Fiction", "Music", "Novels", "Literature", "British Literature"], "asin": "1573225517", "isbn": "1573225517", "isbn13": "9781573225519", "publisher": "Riverhead Books", "author": ["Nick Hornby"], "publishDate": 831279600000, "characters": ["Rob Gordon"], "places": ["London, England"], "ratingHistogram": [2686, 10277, 46060, 82005, 57139], "ratingsCount": 198167, "reviewsCount": 7716, "numPages": 323, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/13214.I_Know_Why_the_Caged_Bird_Sings", "title": "I Know Why the Caged Bird Sings", "titleComplete": "I Know Why the Caged Bird Sings (Maya Angelou's Autobiography, #1)", "description": "Maya Angelou\u2019s debut memoir is a modern American classic beloved worldwide. Her life story is told in the documentary film And Still I Rise, as seen on PBS\u2019s American Masters.Here is a book as joyous and painful, as mysterious and memorable, as childhood itself. I Know Why the Caged Bird Sings captures the longing of lonely children, the brute insult of bigotry, and the wonder of words that can make the world right. Maya Angelou\u2019s debut memoir is a modern American classic beloved worldwide. Sent by their mother to live with their devout, self-sufficient grandmother in a small Southern town, Maya and her brother, Bailey, endure the ache of abandonment and the prejudice of the local \u201cpowhitetrash.\u201d At eight years old and back at her mother\u2019s side in St. Louis, Maya is attacked by a man many times her age\u2014and has to live with the consequences for a lifetime. Years later, in San Francisco, Maya learns that love for herself, the kindness of others, her own strong spirit, and the ideas of great authors (\u201cI met and fell in love with William Shakespeare\u201d) will allow her to be free instead of imprisoned. Poetic and powerful, I Know Why the Caged Bird Sings will touch hearts and change minds for as long as people read.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1327957927i/13214.jpg", "genres": ["African American", "Poetry", "Race", "Biography", "Autobiography", "Classics", "Memoir", "Feminism", "Biography Memoir", "Nonfiction"], "asin": "B00P4JQBIC", "isbn": "0553279378", "isbn13": "9780553279375", "publisher": "Bantam Books", "series": ["Maya Angelou's Autobiography"], "author": ["Maya Angelou"], "publishDate": 752140800000, "characters": ["Bail