{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18460392-all-the-bright-places", "title": "All the Bright Places", "titleComplete": "All the Bright Places", "description": "The Fault in Our Stars meets Eleanor and Park in this exhilarating and heart-wrenching love story about a girl who learns to live from a boy who intends to die.Soon to be a major motion picture starring Elle Fanning!\u00a0Theodore Finch is fascinated by death, and he constantly thinks of ways he might kill himself. But each time, something good, no matter how small, stops him.\u00a0Violet Markey lives for the future, counting the days until graduation, when she can escape her Indiana town and her aching grief in the wake of her sister\u2019s recent death.\u00a0When Finch and Violet meet on the ledge of the bell tower at school, it\u2019s unclear who saves whom. And when they pair up on a project to discover the \u201cnatural wonders\u201d of their state, both Finch and Violet make more important discoveries: It\u2019s only with Violet that Finch can be himself\u2014a weird, funny, live-out-loud guy who\u2019s not such a freak after all. And it\u2019s only with Finch that Violet can forget to count away the days and start living them. But as Violet\u2019s world grows, Finch\u2019s begins to shrink.\u00a0This is an intense, gripping novel perfect for fans of Jay Asher, Rainbow Rowell, John Green, Gayle Forman, and Jenny Downham from a talented new voice in YA, Jennifer Niven.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1404331702i/18460392.jpg", "genres": ["Romance", "Realistic Fiction", "Contemporary", "Mental Illness", "Audiobook", "Fiction", "Mental Health", "Young Adult Contemporary", "Teen", "Young Adult"], "asin": "0385755880", "isbn": "0385755880", "isbn13": "9780385755887", "publisher": "Knopf", "author": ["Jennifer Niven"], "publishDate": 1420531200000, "characters": ["Violet Markey", "Theodore Finch"], "places": ["Indiana"], "ratingHis