{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/394535.Blood_Meridian_or_the_Evening_Redness_in_the_West", "title": "Blood Meridian, or, the Evening Redness in the West", "titleComplete": "Blood Meridian, or, the Evening Redness in the West", "description": "Blood Meridian is an epic novel of the violence and depravity that attended America's westward expansion, brilliantly subverting the conventions of the Western novel and the mythology of the Wild West. Based on historical events that took place on the Texas-Mexico border in the 1850s, it traces the fortunes of the Kid, a fourteen-year-old Tennesseean who stumbles into a nightmarish world where Indians are being murdered and the market for their scalps is thriving.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1701688704i/394535.jpg", "genres": ["Westerns", "Historical Fiction", "Classics", "Historical", "Fiction", "Horror", "Novels", "American", "Literature", "Literary Fiction"], "publisher": "Vintage Books", "author": ["Cormac McCarthy"], "publishDate": 704703600000, "characters": ["The kid", "John Jackson", "Louis Toadvine", "John Joel Glanton", "Judge Holden", "David Brown", "Benjamin Tobin"], "places": ["Texas", "The United States of America", "Mexico"], "ratingHistogram": [3789, 9124, 21812, 42894, 76194], "ratingsCount": 153813, "reviewsCount": 15056, "numPages": 351, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/8664353-unbroken", "title": "Unbroken: A World War II Story of Survival, Resilience and Redemption", "titleComplete": "Unbroken: A World War II Story of Survival, Resilience and Redemption", "description": "On a May afternoon in 1943, an Army Air Forces bomber crashed into the Pacific Ocean and disappeared, leaving only a spray of debris and a slick of oil, gasoline, and blood. Then, on the ocean surface, a face appeared. It was that of a young lieutenant, the plane's bombardier, who was struggling to a life raft and pulling himself aboard. So began one of the most extraordinary odysseys of the Second World War.The lieutenant\u2019s name was Louis Zamperini. In boyhood, he'd been a cunning and incorrigible delinquent, breaking into houses, brawling, and fleeing his home to ride the rails. As a teenager, he had channeled his defiance into running, discovering a prodigious talent that had carried him to the Berlin Olympics and within sight of the four-minute mile. But when war had come, the athlete had become an airman, embarking on a journey that led to his doomed flight, a tiny raft, and a drift into the unknown.Ahead of Zamperini lay thousands of miles of open ocean, leaping sharks, a foundering raft, thirst and starvation, enemy aircraft, and, beyond, a trial even greater. Driven to the limits of endurance, Zamperini would answer desperation with ingenuity; suffering with hope, resolve, and humor; brutality with rebellion. His fate, whether triumph or tragedy, would be suspended on the fraying wire of his will.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1327861115i/8664353.jpg", "genres": ["Biography", "Memoir", "Historical", "War", "Audiobook", "Military Fiction", "World War II", "Biography Memoir", "History", "Nonfiction"], "asin": "1400064163", "isbn": "1400064163", "isbn13": "9781400064168", "publisher": "Random House", "author": ["Laura Hillenbrand"], "publi