{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/130440.Doctor_Zhivago", "title": "Doctor Zhivago", "titleComplete": "Doctor Zhivago", "description": "This epic tale about the effects of the Russian Revolution and its aftermath on a bourgeois family was not published in the Soviet Union until 1987. One of the results of its publication in the West was Pasternak's complete rejection by Soviet authorities; when he was awarded the Nobel Prize for Literature in 1958 he was compelled to decline it. The book quickly became an international best-seller.Dr. Yury Zhivago, Pasternak's alter ego, is a poet, philosopher, and physician whose life is disrupted by the war and by his love for Lara, the wife of a revolutionary. His artistic nature makes him vulnerable to the brutality and harshness of the Bolsheviks. The poems he writes constitute some of the most beautiful writing featured in the novel.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1385508725i/130440.jpg", "genres": ["Romance", "Historical Fiction", "Classics", "Historical", "War", "Fiction", "Novels", "Russian Literature", "Russia", "Literature"], "asin": "0679774386", "isbn": "0679774386", "isbn13": "9780679774389", "publisher": "Pantheon", "author": ["Boris Pasternak", "Manya Harari", "Max Hayward", "John Bayley"], "publishDate": 858672000000, "characters": ["Nicky Dudorov", "Iosif Gimazetdinovich Galiullin", "Nadya Kologrigova", "Pavel Pavlovich Antipov", "Misha Gordon", "Nikolay Nikolayevich Vedenyapin", "Anna Ivanovna Gromeko", "Alexander Alexandrovich Gromeko", "Rodyon Fyodorovich Guishar", "Kuprik Tiverzin", "Kologrivov", "Amalia Karlovna Guishar", "Evgraf Andreevi\u010d Zivago", "Larissa F\u00ebdorovna Antipova", "Victor Ippolitovich Komarovsky", "Marina (Doctor Zhivago)", "Anfim Yefimovitch Samdevyatov", "Antonina Alexandrovna Gromeko", "Markel Shchapov", "Yury Andreyevich Zhivago"], "places": ["Soviet Union", "Moscow", "Siberia", "Russia", "Yuriatin"], "